parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash, and the delay in recall repairs can leave drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: inability to repair or replace airbag inflators
lack of communication from dealerships and manufacturers
and concerns about safety while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring and steering wheel components can cause airbag system failures, loss of horn functionality, and other safety concerns.
The failure of the DSG transmission can cause jerking, hesitation, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents and serious injury.
symptoms: and concerns about safety while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioner can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially on highways. This failure can also result in catastrophic engine damage, requiring expensive repairs.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on
and there may be a loud rattling or grinding noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear main seal can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the rear of the engine
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may experience difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coils can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or running rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCV valve can cause the rear main seal to break, leading to oil leaks and potentially causing accidents due to loss of control.
